OL,7,FA memorial service to honour those
OL,8,Fkilled and injured in the Guildford
OL,9,Fpub bombings has been held to mark the
OL,10,F50th anniversary of the atrocity.
OL,12,FThe Holy Trinity Church in the Surrey
OL,13,Fcity hosted a service to remember the
OL,14,Ffour soldiers and a civilian killed in
OL,15,Fthe attack on October 5, 1974.
OL,17,FSoldiers Caroline Slater, 18, William
OL,18,FForsyth, 18, John Hunter, 17, and Ann
OL,19,FHamilton, 19, and civilian Paul Craig,
OL,20,F21, died in the attack while 65 people
OL,21,Fwere injured.
