OL,7,FThe service was attended by families
OL,8,Fof the victims and survivors, as well
OL,9,Fas civic dignitaries, representatives
OL,10,Fof the Women's Royal Army Corps
OL,11,FAssociation, the Scots Guards
OL,12,FAssociation and members of the public.
OL,14,FRector Canon Simon Butler told the
OL,15,Fcongregation: "Among us all this
OL,16,Fmorning is a quiet and sincere desire
OL,17,Fto bear witness and tribute to those
OL,18,Fwho were killed in our town on perhaps
OL,19,Fthe most terrible night of Guildford's
OL,20,Frecorded history.
