OL,7,F"We are determined not to forget and
OL,8,Fto honour those who fell this part of
OL,9,Fthe country has deep roots with
OL,10,FBritain's military, indeed, that is
OL,11,Fperhaps what made it a target in
OL,12,FOctober 1974
OL,14,FThe Bishop of Guildford Rt Revd Andrew
OL,15,FWatson said: "Along with suffering,
OL,16,Fpain and grief on all sides, bombs
OL,17,Fleft in pubs to cause indiscriminate
OL,18,Fsuffering is unquestionably both bad
OL,19,Fand ugly, a truly evil act, whatever
OL,20,Fthe grievances of those who placed
OL,21,Fthem there.
